metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #37
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: NO ROADMAP #164
metadata.description:
This collection represents the need we have to move forward despite the obstacles that the road may present us.
We identify ourselves with the one who, even without the most optimal conditions, continues on its way until the goal is reached
Web 3.0 is a space that appears to us without a roadmap, so that everyone can explore it and learn.
Even though we only get to have a skateboard, in this journey of work and effort, we will continue asking ourselves until we can at last get it
WEN LAMBO?

+ 100 Roaders + Color variations
+ 50 Backgrounds + Color variations
+ 30 Foreground
+ 50 Animals
+ 25 Foreground elements
+ 10 Police cars on fire

metadata.name: MetaRack #10
metadata.description:
MetaRack is a generative modular synthesizer capable of producing random yet nice sounding patches. MetaRack is written from scratch, with pure sample-by-sample processing and no 3rd party libraries were used for audio handling. Also no samples or prepared audio files were used in this project, everything you hear is generated on-the-fly. The only library involved in MetaRack is p5js which is used for drawing graphical elements.

MetaRack is also a part of a bigger project - we are working on a gallery based on fxhash ecosystem which will allow collectors to connect and arrange their tokens, probably producing derivative NFTs. When launched, MetaRack token holders will receive an exclusive module collection. For more info please read the article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/metarack-modular-synthesizer

Interface:
S - save
L - load
SHIFT - change modulation depth while rotating a knob

@ferluht
@alexexeev
2022

metadata.name: Time Intertwined #125
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
May 2022

An exploration into time and motion. Two linear timelines - structural and surficial - are intertwined. By weaving these timelines at different points in time, almost infinite variations can be made. The changing relationship between the two creates dynamic and unique compositions and challenges the visual perception.

## Guide:
- Please note that the animation responds to window aspect ratio. This is an intentional behavior as part of interactivity. It reproduces the same outcome at the same ratio. 
- To export image at specific size, use URL parameters as below.
- See browser console for more info.
- Tested on MacOS 12.3.1 with Chrome 101.0

## Keyboard Interaction:
- [0] for exhibit. it switches to a different mode every 3 loops.
- [s] to export PNG image. use URL params for dimensions.
- [spacebar] to play/pause animation
- [1 ~ 5] for different play modes
- [1]: all 
- [2]: surficial 
- [3]: constant 
- [4]: all-constant
- [5]: structural
- [h] to toggle hi-DPI mode. (for retina display)

## URL Parameters:
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&mode=exhibit&w=800&st=5.3
- [mode]: play mode (exhibit, all, surficial, constant, all-constant, structural)
- [w]: width. (ex. w=1200)
- [h]: height. (ex. h=600)
- [st]: structural timecode. up to 2 decimals (ex. st=4.31)
- [su]: surficial timecode. up to 2 decimals (ex. su=15.04)
- [co]: constant offset. up to 2 decimals (ex. co=7.4)
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 (or press [h]) for hi-DPI screens.

## License
CC-BY-NC 4.0
Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.
Libraries used: p5, canvas-sketch, canvas-sketch-util, keyframes, easing equations from easings.net

metadata.name: Smoke #46
metadata.description:
Inspired by the hot weather of the city.
Made in August 2022, Milano, Italy.

5 visible Features:
-Mood: tender, bleed, icecream, summer in Milano, evening, futurepunk, acid, love
-Size: small, regular, big
-Density: low, moderate, high, very high
-Speed: slow, moderate, fast
-Emissions: from 2 to 9

Some of the features are very rare, others less, some more common.

The design is being optimized to render at different speeds depending on the size of the window. The smaller the size, the faster the render and lower the detail, viceversa bigger the size, slower the render and higher the detail.
The moire effect of lines that are making the shades of the artwork will look thick with a low resolution, and become finer and more detailed the higher the resolution. You can use this feature to create quick previews or to save very Hi-Resolution images.
To save an image with the size of the window press S once the image is fully rendered.
The fx(hash) thumbnail is saved at 1425px x 1900px.
To save a Hi-Resolution image 3000px x 4000px press H and wait, the page will reload and start to render. Please be patient.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: In the Edge #1
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.
